                <h4 class="alert-primary text-lg-center">Diving Tips</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Drink lots of water and stay hydrated.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Don't hold your breath! Just remember to keep breathing and try to relax.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Scuba diving or breathing underwater can be a strange feeling at first but stick at it as it gets better with each dive.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Try to relax and breathe slowly so you don't consume your air too quickly.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Diving is not a race. Take it slow and steady this helps with your air consumption and you'll see more.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Make sure you are comfortable with your dive buddy .
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Don't drink too much alcohol the night before your dive trip.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        There is nothing more relaxing than laying in sun or shade in between dives and reading, listening to music or just relaxing.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If you buy a new mask you need to clean it out with toothpaste or defog it before using it for the first time.
                    </li>
                    <li class="danger">
                        And most important! Remember not to fly for 24 hours after diving.
                    </li>
                </ul>
